  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Writing Prose for a Playground Page"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Playground pages almost always need prose to introduce the concepts you’re teaching",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "on the page. You use a special kind of Swift comment to mark single lines or blocks",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of text as prose. When a playground page’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "main.swift",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " file is displayed in Swift",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Playgrounds, comments marked as prose are displayed using a proportional font.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-Single-Line-Prose",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add Single-Line Prose",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To add short sections of prose to a page, write a single-line Swift comment that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "starts with a colon (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "//:",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ").",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "//: This line contains a short sentence."
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Comments without the colon are treated as normal Swift comments and are displayed",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in a monospace font. Text that’s outside of any sort of comment is treated as Swift",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "code and runs when you tap Run My Code.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can use markup in prose to add semantic treatments like emphasis and code voice.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For information on supported markup, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Xcode/Reference/xcode_markup_formatting_ref/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016497",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-Multiline-Prose",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add Multiline Prose",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use multiline Swift comments for longer passages. You indicate that a multiline comment",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is prose by adding a colon immediately after the comment’s starting delimiter (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "/*:",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ").",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "/*:",
            "    Roses are `UIColor.red`,",
            "    Violets are 🔵,",
            "    Swift Playgrounds are rad,",
            "    and so are you!",
            "*/"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You don’t need to use a special delimiter to close the comment; use the regular comment",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "closing syntax (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "*/",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ") to finish a multiline prose block.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Reference-Localized-Prose",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Reference Localized Prose",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Localize the content on a page by using the special comment syntax: ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "//:#localized(key: ",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "identifier",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "code": ")",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "identifier",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " key must correspond to an entry in the playground",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "page’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Prose.strings",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " file for each localization folder in the PrivateResources",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "folder.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the following example, the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "ExplanationOfLoops",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " key refers to localized prose",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in a page’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Prose.strings",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " file, in the en.lproj folder under PrivateResources.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "//:#localized(key: \"ExplanationOfLoops\")"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Strings files (localization files with names ending in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".strings",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ") contain multiple",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "key-value pairs, where the key is a phrase you use to identify a block of localized",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "prose, and the value is the localized prose.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The example below shows an English localization of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "ExplanationOfLoops",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "/* An intro to loops. */",
            "\"ExplanationOfLoops\"=\"Use loops to repeat an action multiple times until a condition is met.\";"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The rendered playground page shows the text “Use loops to repeat an action multiple",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "times until a condition is met.” If you provide multiple localizations of your playground",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "book, the text displayed is matched to the locale chosen on the learner’s iPad.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Strings files are a common format used for several kinds of localization and internationalization",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "tasks. For more information about formatting strings files, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Cocoa/Conceptual/LoadingResources/Strings/Strings.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/10000051i-CH6",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/MacOSX/Conceptual/BPInternational/Introduction/Introduction.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/10000171i",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
